\title{Join (preorder)}

\subtree{\taxon{definition}

\p{The join of #{X \subseteq S} in a preorder #{(S, \leq)}, if it exists, is an element #{\vee X \in S} such that }

\ul{
\li{#{\forall x \in X, x  \leq \vee X}}
\li{If #{\forall x \in X, x \leq z}, then #{\vee x \leq z}}
}
}

\p{We often think of the join of a pair of elements and write this #{x \vee y}.}

\p{The join of the empty set #{\vee \varnothing := \top} is a top element #{\forall s \in S: s \leq \top}.}